Package com.complexible.common.memory

Interface Summary
Addressable Interface for an object which is stored off heap and accessible via its address in memory.
HashableObjectSerializer<T> An ObjectSerializer which supports a native hasher for the objects which it serializes
MemoryFlyweight Interface indicating that an object implements the flyweight pattern.
MemoryPool A pool of memory from which allocations can occur.
ObjectSerializer<T> An serializer which can round-trip POJOs to bytes for storage off heap or on disk.
 

Class Summary
AbstractObjectSerializer<T>
HashableObjectSerializerImpl<T>
Memory Utility class around allocating memory via Unsafe
MemoryPools Utilities for MemoryPool
PrimitiveSerializers Serializers for Java primitives
PrimitiveSerializers.LongSerializer  
Reference Reference to an object stored off heap to facilitate flyweight access.
 

Exception Summary
NotEnoughMemoryException An exception to signal that a MemoryPool has been exhausted and cannot allocate any more memory.
